				 Firing cops face CBI grilling
 OUR CORRESPONDENT																								Haldia, Nov. 27: The CBI could question three senior police officers present during the March 14 police firing in Nandigram.																								The then inspector-general (western range), Arun Gupta, DIG (Midnapore range) N. Ramesh Babu and former East Midnapore police chief G.A. Srinivas are under the scanner. Babu and Srinivas have been transferred.																								CBI officials said while it was the constables who fired, the instructions had come from the officers. The senior officials who were in charge of the force at Bhangabera and Tekhali cant avoid responsibility. So, examining them is important, a CBI official said this evening. 																								He is part of the six-member team camping at a Calcutta Port Trust guesthouse here to resume the agencys probe into the firing on the high courts orders. 
